 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Suggested reading on CSS-in-JS</h4>\n<p>If youâ€™re interested in further reading, check out <a href=\"https://speakerdeck.com/vjeux/react-css-in-js\">Christopher â€œvjeuxâ€ Chedeauâ€™s 2014 presentation that sparked this movement</a>\nas well as\n<a href=\"https://medium.com/seek-blog/a-unified-styling-language-d0c208de2660\">Mark Dalgleishâ€™s more recent post â€œA Unified Styling Languageâ€</a>.</p>\n<h3 id=\"other-css-options\"><a href=\"#other-css-options\" aria-label=\"other css options permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Other CSS options</h3>\n<p>Gatsby supports almost every possible styling option (if there isnâ€™t a plugin\nyet for your favorite CSS option,\n<a href=\"/docs/how-to-contribute/\">please contribute one!</a>)</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"/packages/gatsby-plugin-typography/\">Typography.js</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/packages/gatsby-plugin-sass/\">Sass</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/packages/gatsby-plugin-emotion/\">Emotion</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/packages/gatsby-plugin-jss/\">JSS</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/packages/gatsby-plugin-stylus/\">Stylus</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>and more!</p>\n<h2 id=\"whats-coming-next\"><a href=\"#whats-coming-next\" aria-label=\"whats coming next permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path 